            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "When executives publicly proclaim plans to raise future prices or limit production, their comments could amount to illegal ‚Äúinvitations to collude‚Äù under federal antitrust laws ‚Äî because announcing these future plans signals to competitors that they can make such moves in lockstep.",
