      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Less understood by economists, however, is the extent to which corporate consolidation has enabled these price increases. In other words, when just a few companies dominate an industry, are those companies able to increase their prices more than they would in a more competitive environment?",
