          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " suggests it‚Äôs a larger factor than many previously suspected. The study, conducted by the progressive think tank the Roosevelt Institute, looked at price markups ‚Äî essentially, a measure of the gap between prices and input costs.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
